To evaluate the biological effect of anti-N scFv, IL-11-stimulated tyrosine705 phosphorylation of STAT 3 in rat intestinal epithelial IEC-18 cells was examined. IL-11 stimulated STAT 3 phosphorylation that lasted throughout the 60-min test period. In the presence of L9N01 phage (6 × 1010
 cfu), IL-11-induced phosphorylation was completely suppressed. By contrast, the presence of other specific anti-N scFvs exerted no inhibitory effect (Fig. 5
).
